text: Subarachnoid hemorrhage (SAH) is bleeding into the subarachnoid space. This space is the area between the arachnoid membrane and the pia mater, which surrounds the brain. Symptoms may include a severe headache, vomiting, loss of consciousness, fever, and sometimes seizures. Neck stiffness or neck pain are also common. SAH causes troponin levels to rise. ==References== Category:Medical emergencies
title: Subarachnoid hemorrhage
